<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 24 at 5:52AM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...BRIEF MODERATE SNOWFALL THIS MORNING...
A brief burst of moderate snow will impact the Schoharie Valley,
Capital Region, Helderbergs, northern Catskills, upper Mid Hudson
Valley, central Taconics and Berkshires between 545 am and 8 am.
Snowfall rates may briefly reach a half an inch to an inch an
hour. Caution should be used for any travelers or commuters out
there this Christmas Eve morning due to snow covered roads and
reduced visibilities. Conditions should begin to improve after 8
am with only lingering scattered snow showers and flurries.</description>
